
Job Title: Data Analyst
Location: Karachi, Pakistan
Company: Quantix Solutions Pvt. Ltd.
Employment Type: Full-Time
Reports To: Head of Business Intelligence

About Us
At Quantix Solutions, we believe in making smarter decisions powered by data. We are a fast-growing analytics and technology firm based in Karachi, serving clients across finance, healthcare, and retail sectors. We're looking for a passionate Data Analyst who can turn data into actionable insights and drive decision-making across the organization.

Role Overview
As a Data Analyst, you will be responsible for collecting, processing, and analyzing data to uncover trends and provide insights that support strategic business decisions. You will work closely with product, marketing, and operations teams to improve processes and performance through data-backed recommendations.

Key Responsibilities
Analyze large volumes of structured and unstructured data using statistical tools and techniques

Build dashboards and reports to track KPIs and business performance using tools like Power BI or Tableau

Extract data from multiple sources, clean it, and prepare it for analysis

Present complex data findings in a clear and concise manner to stakeholders

Work with cross-functional teams to identify analytical opportunities and optimize workflows

Perform root cause analysis and predictive modeling to support operational improvements

Automate data collection and reporting processes where possible

Required Qualifications
Bachelor's degree in Statistics, Computer Science, Data Science, Economics, or related field

2–4 years of experience as a Data Analyst or in a similar analytical role

Proficiency in SQL and Microsoft Excel

Hands-on experience with data visualization tools such as Power BI, Tableau, or Google Data Studio

Strong analytical and problem-solving skills

Solid understanding of statistical analysis and modeling

Excellent communication skills with the ability to explain data insights to non-technical audiences

Preferred Qualifications
Experience with Python or R for data analysis

Knowledge of database management systems (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB)

Familiarity with cloud data services such as Google BigQuery or AWS Redshift

Understanding of A/B testing and business experimentation techniques

Certification in data analytics or business intelligence tools is a plus

Perks and Benefits
Competitive market salary

Annual performance bonuses

Flexible work hours and occasional remote work options

Medical insurance for self and dependents

Learning stipends for online courses or certifications

Fun, data-driven work culture with regular team activities

How to Apply
Send your updated resume and a short cover letter to careers@quantixsolutions.pk with the subject line: Application for Data Analyst – Karachi. Attach links to your data projects, dashboards, or GitHub (if available).
